attributes.value: Hybrid drumming is becoming more common as time goes on, and an essential part of most professional drummers out there. Being proficient with electronics has become a must for most professional drummers out there, as an important tool of the trade, as well as a way to create a very unique voice. In this video, Larnell will show you how he uses electronics to spice up his playing and create a very unique sound on the kit that he can call his own.
In this lesson, Heather is going to teach you how to calm your nerves before live gigs and recording sessions, so you're able to focus on the music and be the best musician possible.

In this lesson Jared breaks down the types of students he encounters most often and how they go about becoming better at the drums. Make sure to check it out so you know exactly how to get better as well!

In this lesson, Raghav is going to teach you how to be the backbone of any bland you play with, by teaching you exercises and giving you tips that will help you keep perfect time and make any song feel awesome!
In this lesson, Kyle is going to help you get the most out of your electronic drum-set so if you ever switch to an acoustic set or go back and forth, they feel pretty much the same to you.

As part of The Beatles, Ringo Starr was hugely influencial in the world of drumming. In this lesson, Gregg Bissonette, who has been playing and touring with Ringo for over 10 years, breaks down exactly why Ringo is such an iconic musician.
In this lesson, Brandon Toews is going to teach you how to play five styles of drumming that you're probably unfamiliar with: the flat tire shuffle, zouk, afoxÃª, poinciana, and go-go.
In this lesson, Raghav will teach you a quick warm-up routine he likes to bust out whenever he doesn't have much time to practice or to work and improve on some of his core hand-technique skills.
In this lesson, Gregg Bissonette is going to teach you how to play single stroke rolls between the hands and the feet.
In this lesson, Dorothea Taylor will teach you how to properly develop your wrists to play some awesome-sounding double-stroke rolls.
In this lesson, Jared is going to talk about 11 things drummers are scared of when it comes to playing live and how to deal with these issues in a good way.
In this lesson, Gregg Bissonette is going to share his method for learning songs by ear.
In this lesson, Kyle will teach you a very cool snare solo he came up in honor of Charley Wilcoxon and his lauded rudimental solo book: The All-American Drummer.
In this lesson, Ash Pearson will teach you how to play five essential heavy metal chops.

In this lesson, Gregg Bissonette is going to teach you his favorite drum lick: the blushda. But to spice it up a little bit he's going to teach you his own version of it, which he calls the extended blushda.
In this lesson, Gill Sharone is going to share his method for learning songs by ear.

In this lesson, Juan Mendoza is going to teach you five Latin grooves that you need to learn if you want to become a professional drummer. This includes the cha cha, the mambo, the nanigo, the mozambique, and the songo.
In this lesson, Juan is going to teach you how to play and develop 5 essential hybrid rudiments: the herta, the blushda, the choo choo, flam grandpas, and the stutter.
In this lesson, Heather Thomas will teach you five tips that will greatly improve your ability to drum very well while singing along.
In this lesson, Ash Pearson will teach you how to play five iconic heavy metal beats.
